
        <html xmlns:o='urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office' xmlns:w='urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40'>
        <head><meta charset='utf-8'><title>Project Documentation</title>
        <style>
          body { font-family: 'Segoe UI', Calibri, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; color: #1e293b; max-width: 800px; margin: auto; padding: 40px; }
          h1 { color: #4f46e5; border-bottom: 3px solid #4f46e5; padding-bottom: 15px; font-size: 28pt; }
          h2 { color: #0891b2; margin-top: 40px; border-bottom: 2px solid #e2e8f0; padding-bottom: 8px; font-size: 20pt; }
          h3 { color: #334155; margin-top: 25px; font-size: 16pt; border-left: 4px solid #4f46e5; padding-left: 15px; }
          p { margin-bottom: 15px; text-align: justify; }
          .executive-summary { background: #f8fafc; padding: 25px; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; margin: 25px 0; font-style: italic; color: #475569; }
          .priority-high { background: #fef2f2; color: #b91c1c; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 9pt; }
          .priority-medium { background: #fffbeb; color: #b45309; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 9pt; }
          .priority-low { background: #f0fdf4; color: #15803d; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 9pt; }
          table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 25px 0; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden; }
          th { background-color: #f1f5f9; color: #475569; font-weight: bold; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 9pt; letter-spacing: 0.05em; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; padding: 12px; }
          td { border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; padding: 12px; text-align: left; vertical-align: top; font-size: 10pt; }
          code { font-family: 'Consolas', monospace; background: #f1f5f9; padding: 2px 5px; border-radius: 4px; color: #be185d; }
          .footer { font-size: 9pt; color: #94a3b8; text-align: center; margin-top: 80px; border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0; padding-top: 20px; }
        </style>
        </head><body>
      <h1>Agent Project v1</h1><p><strong>Vision:</strong> Orchestrated Architecture & Product Strategy</p><h2>1. Requirement Specification (BRD)</h2><div class="executive-summary"><strong>Project Overview:</strong><br/>The proposed project entails the design and development of a centralized, highly responsive personal data and portfolio website. This digital platform will serve as the authoritative source of truth for the individual's professional identity, showcasing their skills, career trajectory, educational background, and portfolio of work. By consolidating this information into a single, accessible location, the platform aims to elevate the individual's professional brand and streamline information sharing with prospective employers, clients, and collaborators. Furthermore, the website will be engineered to provide a seamless user experience across all devices, ensuring that visitors can easily navigate and consume the presented data. The value proposition lies in creating a compelling digital footprint that not only highlights past achievements but also facilitates future career opportunities through integrated contact mechanisms and downloadable assets.</div><h3>Business Objectives</h3><p>1. Establish a robust and professional online presence to enhance personal branding. 2. Centralize professional data, including work history, skills, and project portfolios, to serve as a dynamic digital resume. 3. Facilitate direct communication with recruiters, potential clients, and industry peers via secure contact channels. 4. Provide a scalable platform that can grow alongside the individual's career progression.</p><h3>Scope</h3><strong>In Scope:</strong><ul><li>Responsive user interface design</li><li>Dynamic project portfolio gallery</li><li>Downloadable resume/CV functionality</li><li>Secure contact form with email routing</li><li>Skills and experience timeline</li><li>Basic SEO optimization</li><li>Admin dashboard for content management</li></ul><strong>Out of Scope:</strong><ul><li>E-commerce capabilities</li><li>Multi-user registration or social networking features</li><li>Complex blog with user commenting</li><li>Third-party advertising integrations</li></ul><h3>Stakeholders</h3><ul><li>Site Owner (Primary Administrator)</li><li>End Users (Recruiters, Hiring Managers, Potential Clients)</li><li>Development Team</li><li>Quality Assurance Team</li></ul><h3>Functional Requirements</h3><ul><li>1. The system must display a comprehensive professional biography and summary.</li><li>2. The system must provide a chronological timeline of work experience and education.</li><li>3. The system must feature a dedicated portfolio section to showcase past projects with descriptions and media.</li><li>4. The system must allow visitors to filter portfolio projects by skill or technology category.</li><li>5. The system must include a secure contact form requiring name, email, and message fields.</li><li>6. The system must automatically route submitted contact forms to the Site Owner's designated email address.</li><li>7. The system must provide a direct download link for the Site Owner's current resume/CV in PDF format.</li><li>8. The system must include an administrative interface accessible via secure login credentials.</li><li>9. The system must allow the Administrator to create, read, update, and delete (CRUD) portfolio entries.</li><li>10. The system must allow the Administrator to update the skills list and proficiency levels.</li><li>11. The system must support the integration of links to external professional profiles.</li><li>12. The system must display a success notification to the user upon successful submission of the contact form.</li><li>13. The system must validate all user inputs on the contact form to prevent spam and errors.</li><li>14. The system must allow the Administrator to upload and manage media assets for the portfolio.</li><li>15. The system must provide a toggle for dark mode and light mode viewing preferences.</li></ul><h3>Non-Functional Requirements</h3><ul><li>Performance: The website must load within 3 seconds on standard broadband connections.</li><li>Accessibility: The user interface must comply with WCAG 2.1 AA standards to ensure usability for individuals with disabilities.</li><li>Security: All data transmissions, particularly contact form submissions and admin logins, must be encrypted via HTTPS/TLS.</li><li>Responsiveness: The application must render flawlessly across desktop, tablet, and mobile viewports.</li><li>Reliability: The hosting infrastructure must guarantee 99.9% uptime.</li></ul><h3>User Stories</h3><table><tr><th width="10%">ID</th><th width="30%">Story</th><th width="35%">Detailed Description</th><th width="15%">Priority</th></tr><tr>
              <td><strong>#US-01</strong></td>
              <td>As a prospective employer, I want to view a summary of the individual's professional background so that I can quickly assess their qualifications.</td>
              <td>Ensures the core value proposition of the site is immediately apparent to visitors.
                  <div style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 9pt; color: #64748b;"><strong>Acceptance Criteria:</strong>
                  <ul><li>Bio section is visible on the homepage</li><li>Text is legible and professionally formatted</li></ul></div>
              </td>
              <td><span class="priority-high">High</span></td>
            </tr><tr>
              <td><strong>#US-02</strong></td>
              <td>As a recruiter, I want to download a PDF version of the resume so that I can share it with my hiring team.</td>
              <td>Facilitates offline sharing and integration into Applicant Tracking Systems.
                  <div style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 9pt; color: #64748b;"><strong>Acceptance Criteria:</strong>
                  <ul><li>Download button is prominently displayed</li><li>Clicking the button initiates a PDF download</li><li>The downloaded file is the most recent version</li></ul></div>
              </td>
              <td><span class="priority-high">High</span></td>
            </tr><tr>
              <td><strong>#US-03</strong></td>
              <td>As a potential client, I want to submit an inquiry via a contact form so that I can discuss a potential project.</td>
              <td>Drives the primary conversion goal of the website by enabling direct communication.
                  <div style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 9pt; color: #64748b;"><strong>Acceptance Criteria:</strong>
                  <ul><li>Form includes Name, Email, and Message fields</li><li>Form validates email format</li><li>User receives a success message upon submission</li></ul></div>
              </td>
              <td><span class="priority-high">High</span></td>
            </tr><tr>
              <td><strong>#US-04</strong></td>
              <td>As a peer, I want to filter the project portfolio by specific technologies so that I can see relevant examples of work.</td>
              <td>Enhances user experience by allowing visitors to find specific information quickly.
                  <div style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 9pt; color: #64748b;"><strong>Acceptance Criteria:</strong>
                  <ul><li>Filter tags are visible above the portfolio gallery</li><li>Clicking a tag updates the displayed projects dynamically</li><li>Multiple tags can be selected or deselected</li></ul></div>
              </td>
              <td><span class="priority-medium">Medium</span></td>
            </tr><tr>
              <td><strong>#US-05</strong></td>
              <td>As the Site Owner, I want to log into a secure admin dashboard so that I can manage my website content.</td>
              <td>Provides the foundation for content management and site maintenance.
                  <div style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 9pt; color: #64748b;"><strong>Acceptance Criteria:</strong>
                  <ul><li>Login page requires username and password</li><li>Authentication is secure</li><li>Successful login redirects to the dashboard</li></ul></div>
              </td>
              <td><span class="priority-high">High</span></td>
            </tr><tr>
              <td><strong>#US-06</strong></td>
              <td>As the Site Owner, I want to add a new project to my portfolio so that my website reflects my latest work.</td>
              <td>Ensures the portfolio remains current and relevant without requiring code changes.
                  <div style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 9pt; color: #64748b;"><strong>Acceptance Criteria:</strong>
                  <ul><li>Admin can input project title, description, and upload images</li><li>Admin can assign technology tags</li><li>Saved project immediately appears on the live site</li></ul></div>
              </td>
              <td><span class="priority-high">High</span></td>
            </tr><tr>
              <td><strong>#US-07</strong></td>
              <td>As a mobile user, I want the website layout to adapt to my screen size so that I can easily read the content without zooming.</td>
              <td>Addresses the significant portion of web traffic originating from mobile devices.
                  <div style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 9pt; color: #64748b;"><strong>Acceptance Criteria:</strong>
                  <ul><li>Navigation collapses into a hamburger menu on small screens</li><li>Images scale proportionally</li><li>Text remains readable without horizontal scrolling</li></ul></div>
              </td>
              <td><span class="priority-high">High</span></td>
            </tr><tr>
              <td><strong>#US-08</strong></td>
              <td>As the Site Owner, I want to update my list of skills and proficiency levels so that my profile accurately reflects my current capabilities.</td>
              <td>Allows the site owner to keep their professional data accurate as they learn new technologies.
                  <div style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 9pt; color: #64748b;"><strong>Acceptance Criteria:</strong>
                  <ul><li>Admin can add, edit, or remove skills</li><li>Admin can adjust a visual indicator of proficiency for each skill</li><li>Changes reflect immediately on the frontend</li></ul></div>
              </td>
              <td><span class="priority-medium">Medium</span></td>
            </tr><tr>
              <td><strong>#US-09</strong></td>
              <td>As a visitor, I want to click on social media icons so that I can view the individual's LinkedIn and GitHub profiles.</td>
              <td>Expands the user's professional footprint by connecting the site to broader networks.
                  <div style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 9pt; color: #64748b;"><strong>Acceptance Criteria:</strong>
                  <ul><li>Icons are clearly visible in the header or footer</li><li>Links open in a new browser tab</li><li>URLs are correctly routed to the respective profiles</li></ul></div>
              </td>
              <td><span class="priority-low">Low</span></td>
            </tr><tr>
              <td><strong>#US-10</strong></td>
              <td>As the Site Owner, I want to view a log of submitted contact messages in the admin dashboard so that I have a backup in case of email delivery failure.</td>
              <td>Provides redundancy for critical communications and helps manage inquiries.
                  <div style="margin-top: 8px; font-size: 9pt; color: #64748b;"><strong>Acceptance Criteria:</strong>
                  <ul><li>Dashboard includes a Messages section</li><li>Messages display sender name, email, date, and content</li><li>Admin can mark messages as read or delete them</li></ul></div>
              </td>
              <td><span class="priority-medium">Medium</span></td>
            </tr></table><h3>Assumptions & Constraints</h3><ul><li>Assumption: The Site Owner will provide all initial content, including text, images, and resume files, prior to development.</li><li>Assumption: The platform will be managed by a single administrative user.</li><li>Constraint: The project must be delivered within the specified budget and timeline constraints.</li><li>Constraint: The system will rely on standard web hosting environments without requiring specialized enterprise infrastructure.</li><li>Constraint: The website will be built using modern, widely-supported web standards (HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript).</li></ul><br clear=all style='mso-break-type:section-break'><h2>2. System Design Blueprint</h2><h3>High-Level Design</h3><p><strong>Architecture Overview:</strong><br/>The system follows a modern decoupled Client-Server architecture. The frontend is a responsive Single Page Application (SPA) or Server-Side Rendered (SSR) application built with Next.js/React, ensuring optimal SEO and fast load times. It communicates via RESTful APIs with a Node.js/Express backend. The backend handles business logic, authentication (JWT), and interfaces with a PostgreSQL relational database for structured data storage (projects, skills, messages, experience). Media assets (portfolio images, resume PDF) are stored in a cloud object storage service like AWS S3. An external email service (e.g., SendGrid) is integrated to route contact form submissions to the Site Owner's email address.</p><p><strong>Data Flow:</strong><br/>1. Public User Flow: A visitor accesses the site; the frontend fetches portfolio, skills, and experience data from the backend API, which retrieves it from the PostgreSQL database. Images are served directly from AWS S3 via CDN. 2. Contact Flow: A visitor submits the contact form. The frontend validates inputs and sends a POST request to the API. The API saves the message to the database, triggers the Email Service to notify the owner, and returns a success response to the frontend. 3. Admin Flow: The Site Owner logs in via the Auth module, receiving a JWT. The owner uses the Admin Dashboard to send authenticated CRUD requests to the API to update projects, skills, or view saved messages.</p><p><strong>Tech Stack:</strong><br/>Frontend: Next.js, React, Tailwind CSS (for responsive design and dark/light mode). Backend: Node.js, Express.js. Database: PostgreSQL. Authentication: JSON Web Tokens (JWT) and bcrypt for password hashing. Storage: AWS S3. DevOps: Docker, GitHub Actions for CI/CD, Vercel for frontend hosting, Render or AWS ECS for backend hosting.</p><h3>Low-Level Design</h3><p><strong>Component Design:</strong><br/>1. Frontend Core: Utilizes React Context for global state management (ThemeContext for Dark/Light mode, AuthContext for Admin sessions). Components are modularized into UI primitives (Buttons, Inputs, Cards) and Feature components (ProjectCard, SkillBar, TimelineItem). 2. Backend API: Follows a Controller-Service-Repository pattern. Controllers handle HTTP requests and responses. Services contain business logic (e.g., validating portfolio data, formatting emails). Repositories handle database queries using an ORM like Prisma or Sequelize. 3. Auth Module: Implements a secure login endpoint that verifies credentials against hashed passwords in the DB and issues a short-lived JWT and a secure HttpOnly refresh cookie. 4. Media Upload Module: Uses Multer for handling multipart/form-data, validating file types, and streaming uploads directly to AWS S3, returning the public URL to be saved in the database.</p><p><strong>UI Structure:</strong><br/>RootLayout
 ├── ThemeProvider
 ├── NavigationBar (Logo, Links, ThemeToggle, MobileHamburger)
 ├── PublicPages
 │    ├── HeroSection (Bio, ResumeDownloadButton)
 │    ├── ExperienceTimeline (TimelineItems)
 │    ├── PortfolioSection (FilterTags, ProjectGrid, ProjectCard)
 │    └── ContactSection (ContactForm, SuccessNotification)
 ├── AdminPages (Protected Route)
 │    ├── AdminSidebar
 │    ├── DashboardOverview
 │    ├── ProjectManager (ProjectForm, ImageUploader)
 │    ├── SkillManager (SkillList, ProficiencySlider)
 │    └── MessageInbox (MessageList, MessageDetail)
 └── Footer (SocialMediaLinks)</p><h4>API Endpoints</h4><table><tr><th>Method</th><th>Endpoint</th><th>Request</th><th>Response</th></tr><tr><td><strong>POST</strong></td><td><code>/api/auth/login</code></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{
  "username": "string",
  "password": "string"
}</pre></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{
  "token": "string",
  "user": {
    "id": "number",
    "username": "string"
  }
}</pre></td></tr><tr><td><strong>GET</strong></td><td><code>/api/portfolio</code></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{}</pre></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">[
  {
    "id": "number",
    "title": "string",
    "description": "string",
    "imageUrl": "string",
    "tags": [
      "string"
    ]
  }
]</pre></td></tr><tr><td><strong>POST</strong></td><td><code>/api/portfolio</code></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{
  "title": "string",
  "description": "string",
  "imageUrl": "string",
  "tags": [
    "string"
  ]
}</pre></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{
  "id": "number",
  "title": "string",
  "message": "Project created successfully"
}</pre></td></tr><tr><td><strong>PUT</strong></td><td><code>/api/portfolio/:id</code></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{
  "title": "string",
  "description": "string",
  "imageUrl": "string",
  "tags": [
    "string"
  ]
}</pre></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{
  "message": "Project updated successfully"
}</pre></td></tr><tr><td><strong>DELETE</strong></td><td><code>/api/portfolio/:id</code></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{}</pre></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{
  "message": "Project deleted successfully"
}</pre></td></tr><tr><td><strong>GET</strong></td><td><code>/api/skills</code></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{}</pre></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">[
  {
    "id": "number",
    "name": "string",
    "proficiency": "number"
  }
]</pre></td></tr><tr><td><strong>POST</strong></td><td><code>/api/skills</code></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{
  "name": "string",
  "proficiency": "number"
}</pre></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{
  "id": "number",
  "message": "Skill added successfully"
}</pre></td></tr><tr><td><strong>POST</strong></td><td><code>/api/contact</code></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{
  "name": "string",
  "email": "string",
  "message": "string"
}</pre></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{
  "message": "Message sent successfully"
}</pre></td></tr><tr><td><strong>GET</strong></td><td><code>/api/messages</code></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{}</pre></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">[
  {
    "id": "number",
    "name": "string",
    "email": "string",
    "content": "string",
    "isRead": "boolean",
    "createdAt": "string"
  }
]</pre></td></tr><tr><td><strong>PATCH</strong></td><td><code>/api/messages/:id/read</code></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{
  "isRead": "boolean"
}</pre></td><td><pre style="font-size: 8pt; white-space: pre-wrap;">{
  "message": "Message status updated"
}</pre></td></tr></table><br clear=all style='mso-break-type:section-break'><h2>3. Development Documentation</h2><h3>Technology Stack</h3><p>Frontend: Next.js, React, Tailwind CSS, Zustand (State Management), Framer Motion (Animations), Lucide React (Icons). Backend: Node.js, Express.js. Database: PostgreSQL. Authentication: JSON Web Tokens (JWT) and bcrypt. Storage: AWS S3. External Integrations: SendGrid API (Email Routing). DevOps: Docker, GitHub Actions, Vercel, Render or AWS ECS.</p><h3>Project Structure</h3><pre style="font-size: 8pt; background: #f8fafc; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Root Directory -> frontend/ (contains App.tsx, UI components for Public and Admin pages, Tailwind styles, and Zustand store) -> backend/ (contains server.js, Express routes, JWT authentication middleware, and mock/PostgreSQL database integration) -> infrastructure/ (contains Dockerfiles and CI/CD workflow configurations).</pre><h3>Setup Instructions</h3><p>Step 1: Clone the repository to your local machine. Step 2: Navigate to the backend directory, run 'npm install' to install dependencies, create a .env file with required backend variables, and run 'npm start' to launch the Express server on port 3001. Step 3: Navigate to the frontend directory, run 'npm install', create a .env file setting NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE to http://localhost:3001, and run 'npm run dev' to start the React application. Step 4: Access the frontend via the local development server URL provided in the terminal.</p><h3>Environment Variables</h3><p>PORT: The port number for the backend server (default 3001). DATABASE_URL: Connection string for the PostgreSQL database. JWT_SECRET: Secret key used for signing and verifying JSON Web Tokens. SENDGRID_API_KEY: API key for routing contact form submissions to email. OWNER_EMAIL: The destination email address for contact notifications. AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID and AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY: Credentials for uploading media to AWS S3. AWS_S3_BUCKET_NAME: The target S3 bucket for portfolio images and resumes. NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE: The frontend variable pointing to the backend API URL.</p><h3>Deployment Overview</h3><p>Frontend Deployment: Hosted on Vercel or AWS CloudFront to leverage global CDN distribution, fast load times, and seamless Next.js SSR/SPA support. Backend Deployment: Containerized using Docker and deployed to a scalable cloud platform like Render or AWS ECS. Database: A managed PostgreSQL instance such as AWS RDS or Supabase. Storage: AWS S3 is used for hosting user-uploaded portfolio images and the downloadable resume PDF. CI/CD: GitHub Actions is recommended to automate testing, Docker image building, and deployment pipelines upon pushing to the main branch.</p><br clear=all style='mso-break-type:section-break'><h2>4. Quality Assurance & Verification</h2><h3>Test Plan</h3><p><strong>Scope:</strong> Testing covers the frontend UI/UX, backend API endpoints, Admin Dashboard functionality, Contact Form submission, Portfolio filtering, and Dark/Light mode toggling. Excluded: Real email delivery (currently mocked) and persistent database testing (using in-memory mock DB).</p><p><strong>Strategy:</strong> A hybrid approach utilizing manual exploratory testing for UI/UX and responsive design, automated API testing for backend endpoints, and End-to-End (E2E) testing for critical user journeys such as Admin authentication and CRUD operations.</p><div class="executive-summary"><strong>Execution Summary:</strong><br/>Testing of the Personal Portfolio application is complete. The core functionalities including public data display, portfolio filtering, contact form submission, and admin CRUD operations are working as intended. The application is highly responsive and the dark/light mode toggle functions perfectly. However, a few minor defects were identified regarding placeholder links and mobile menu animations that require developer attention before final production release.</div><h3>Test Cases</h3><table><tr><th width="10%">ID</th><th width="20%">Description</th><th width="30%">Steps</th><th width="15%">Expected</th><th width="15%">Actual</th><th width="10%">Status</th></tr><tr>
              <td><strong>TC-01</strong></td>
              <td>Verify homepage loads and displays professional bio</td>
              <td><ol style="margin:0; padding-left:15px;"><li>Navigate to the application root URL.</li><li>Observe the Hero section.</li><li>Verify the presence of the professional bio and 'Available for new opportunities' badge.</li></ol></td>
              <td>Homepage loads successfully, displaying the bio, name, and professional summary.</td>
              <td>Homepage loaded successfully with all bio elements visible.</td>
              <td style="color: #15803d; font-weight: bold;">PASSED</td>
            </tr><tr>
              <td><strong>TC-02</strong></td>
              <td>Verify resume download functionality</td>
              <td><ol style="margin:0; padding-left:15px;"><li>Navigate to the homepage.</li><li>Click the 'Download CV' button in the Hero section.</li></ol></td>
              <td>A PDF file named 'Resume.pdf' is downloaded to the user's device.</td>
              <td>A mock PDF blob named 'Resume.pdf' is downloaded. Note: Needs real PDF integration.</td>
              <td style="color: #15803d; font-weight: bold;">PASSED</td>
            </tr><tr>
              <td><strong>TC-03</strong></td>
              <td>Verify contact form validation for empty fields</td>
              <td><ol style="margin:0; padding-left:15px;"><li>Scroll to the Contact section.</li><li>Leave Name, Email, and Message fields blank.</li><li>Click 'Send Message'.</li></ol></td>
              <td>Form submission is prevented, and HTML5 validation prompts appear for required fields.</td>
              <td>HTML5 validation prevented submission and highlighted the empty Name field.</td>
              <td style="color: #15803d; font-weight: bold;">PASSED</td>
            </tr><tr>
              <td><strong>TC-04</strong></td>
              <td>Verify successful contact form submission</td>
              <td><ol style="margin:0; padding-left:15px;"><li>Scroll to the Contact section.</li><li>Enter 'Jane Doe' in Name.</li><li>Enter 'jane@example.com' in Email.</li><li>Enter 'Test message' in Message.</li><li>Click 'Send Message'.</li></ol></td>
              <td>Button shows 'Sending...', then a success message 'Message sent successfully!' appears.</td>
              <td>Button showed 'Sending...' and success message appeared. Backend logged the mock email.</td>
              <td style="color: #15803d; font-weight: bold;">PASSED</td>
            </tr><tr>
              <td><strong>TC-05</strong></td>
              <td>Verify portfolio filtering by technology tags</td>
              <td><ol style="margin:0; padding-left:15px;"><li>Scroll to the Portfolio section.</li><li>Click on the 'React' filter tag.</li><li>Observe the displayed projects.</li></ol></td>
              <td>Only projects containing the 'React' tag are displayed.</td>
              <td>Gallery dynamically updated to show only 'E-Commerce Platform' and 'AI Content Generator'.</td>
              <td style="color: #15803d; font-weight: bold;">PASSED</td>
            </tr><tr>
              <td><strong>TC-06</strong></td>
              <td>Verify Dark/Light mode toggle</td>
